<title>UK: C&amp;W stock soars after HK Telecom sale.</title>
<headline>C&amp;W stock soars after HK Telecom sale.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Cable and Wireless Plc soared 73.5p to an unofficial close of 571p, after news it had sold a 5.5 percent stake in Hong Kong Telecommunications Ltd to state-owned China Telecom for HK$14.25 per share. Hong Kong Telecom shares were quoted in London at HK$18.9 before the announcement.</p>
<p>Trade in C&amp;W stock hit almost 20 million after news of the sale, which ended months of speculation. The shares had been trading in the region of 540p -- 33.5p ahead -- before the announcement.</p>
